gmd:supplementalInformation.gco:CharacterString:
&lt;b&gt;Desired product specifications&lt;/b&gt; &lt;br&gt;
Products shall be&lt;br&gt;

- TOA reflectances (~L1A)&lt;br&gt;
- L3 (bi-weekly and bi-monthly composites from orthorectified, atmospherically-corrected surface reflectances)&lt;br&gt;
- Geolocation accuracy &lt;80-100m for MR products&lt;br&gt;
- Geolocation accuracy &lt;300m for LR resolution data&lt;br&gt;
- DEM to be used for bi-weekly/bi-monthly composites = GETASSE30&lt;br&gt;
- Projection: "lat-lon geographic WGS 84" for composites&lt;br&gt;
- Format: GeoTIFF for MR composites; HDF for LR composites&lt;br&gt;
- Pre-processing: 300m delivery of bi-weekly and bi-monthly syntheses matching at least the quality achieved for GLOBCOVER (remaining atmospheric noise should not be perceivable in time series profiles of bi-weekly products, spatial patterns due to atmospheric effects must be an order of magnitude lower than the spatial patterns due to the natural landscape).&lt;br&gt;
- SWIR useful for free water detection, mixed vegetation &amp; water detection, discrimination cloud/snow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Delivery specification&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Start delivery&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;br&gt;
- 03/2009 delivery for archive data (Europe)&lt;br&gt;
- 12/2008 for new acquisitions (Africa)&lt;br&gt;
- 12/2008 for new acquisitions (Europe)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;


&lt;b&gt;Timeliness&lt;/b&gt; (negotiation ongoing):&lt;br&gt;
- Level1A TOA reflectance in NRT (alternative: Fast24h)&lt;br&gt;
- Level3 daily composite in Fast24h&lt;br&gt;
- Normal for composites (10-daily, bi-weekly and bi-monthly)&lt;br&gt;
- Cumulative for archive&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

